    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-08T17:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-08T17:25:00-05:00" n="177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/3860: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-08T18:25:00-04:00"
                            >May 8, 1943—6:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. A–1271. Reference Embassy’s Airgram A–822, May 1, 12:30 p.m. Your
                    recommendation to send sugar insurance investigator to Habana to examine
                    insurance deal has received careful consideration of the Department and CCC,
                    which agency awaits a reply to its letter of April 20 to Institute, mentioned in
                    Department’s instruction No. 1551 of April 26.<note n="50" xml:id="d177fn50"
                        >Neither printed.</note> Although arrangement was announced two months ago,
                    details have not been submitted and CCC prefers to have review of matter take
                    place in Washington with full responsibility on Institute for presenting
                    satisfactory coverage. When facts are before CCC, a speedy decision can be
                    reached.</p>
                <p>You are requested to ascertain from Institute how soon CCC may expect reply,
                    which, of course, should be expedited.</p>
                <p>(Banking arrangements have already been made by CCC for June first payment.)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
